usage: docbuilder.py [-h] [-i INPUT] [-o OUTPUT] [-d DIRECTORY] [--indent]
                     [--mkdocs] [-v] [-q]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i INPUT, --input INPUT
                        The input file. Normally, a *.pylit file.
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        The output file name, without file extension.
  -d DIRECTORY, --directory DIRECTORY
                        Set the output directory.
  --indent              Indent Markdown
  --mkdocs              Make Docbuilder aware you want to use mkdocs.
  -v, --verbose         Print more information to the console
  -q, --quiet           Clobber existing files without asking.
